Enum SystemStateFeature

All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<SystemStateFeature>
public enum SystemStateFeature
extends java.lang.Enum<SystemStateFeature>

Enum for all features that can be accessed from system state. For each type either info() or state() needs to be implemented. Note that the default implementation of state() uses the information provided by info(). In particular, OK is returned if info() is true, ERROR is returned otherwise. In case of an exception in info() the error message is used to provide details.

as
